            <fr:title text="Metric Space">Metric Space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
    A <html:strong>metric space</html:strong> is a pair <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, d)]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a set and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d : X \times  X \to  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is a function called a <html:strong>metric</html:strong>, satisfying for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y, z \in  X]]></fr:tex>:
</html:p>
            <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x, y) \geq  0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x, y) = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = y]]></fr:tex> (positive definiteness).</html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x, y) = d(y, x)]]></fr:tex> (symmetry).</html:li>
    <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x, z) \leq  d(x, y) + d(y, z)]]></fr:tex> (triangle inequality).</html:li></html:ol>
            <html:p>
    Every metric space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, d)]]></fr:tex> induces a <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topology</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, called the <html:strong>metric topology</html:strong>, where the open sets are unions of <fr:link href="/gtop-000S/" title="Open Ball" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/" display-uri="gtop-000S" type="local">open balls</fr:link>.
</html:p>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>11</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>gtop-000S</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/gtop-000S/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Open Ball">Open Ball</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, d)]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/gtop-0003/" title="Metric Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0003/" display-uri="gtop-0003" type="local">metric space</fr:link>. The <html:strong>open ball</html:strong> centered at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex> with radius <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  > 0]]></fr:tex> is
</html:p>
                <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[B(x, \epsilon ) = \left \{ y \in  X : d(x, y) < \epsilon  \right \}]]></fr:tex>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>11</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000R/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>gtop-000R</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/gtop-000R/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Metric Topology">Metric Topology</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Notation</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
A <fr:link href="/gtop-0003/" title="Metric Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0003/" display-uri="gtop-0003" type="local">metric space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, d)]]></fr:tex> induces a <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topology</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\tau _d]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> by declaring <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \in  \tau _d]]></fr:tex> if and only if for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  U]]></fr:tex> there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon  > 0]]></fr:tex> such that the <fr:link href="/gtop-000S/" title="Open Ball" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/" display-uri="gtop-000S" type="local">open ball</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B(x, \epsilon ) \subseteq  U]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
                <html:p>
That is, a metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> induces a topology through the following chain:
</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li>The metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> defines <fr:link href="/gtop-000S/" title="Open Ball" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/" display-uri="gtop-000S" type="local">open balls</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B(x, \epsilon )]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li>Open balls generate <fr:link href="/gtop-0005/" title="Open Set" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0005/" display-uri="gtop-0005" type="local">open sets</fr:link>: a set is open if and only if it is an arbitrary union of open balls.</html:li>
<html:li>The collection of all open sets forms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\tau _d]]></fr:tex>, a valid <fr:link href="/gtop-0002/" title="Topological Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0002/" display-uri="gtop-0002" type="local">topology</fr:link>.</html:li></html:ol>
                <html:p>
Every metric space is a topological space, but not every topological space arises from a metric. A topological space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, \tau )]]></fr:tex> is called <html:strong>metrizable</html:strong> if there exists a metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\tau  = \tau _d]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
